<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-34-0898 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper focussed on cost functions for individual establishments usingengineering estimates of the relevant technologies and their costs. Inpollution control and regulatory situations, the range of gradually risingcosts and approximate location of large increases in cost for a smallgain in abatement are sufficient data to help design control programs.The systematic deriviation of relevant cost functions and their use inevaluations and assessments can ensure that these programs are implementedfairly and efficiently. 9 refs., 3 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>